==Dialogue==
{{Dialogue Start}}
:<!--Trigger PerformanceE 504014001: Config/Level/Mission/5040140/Act/Act504014001.json-->
:'''Aglaea:''' The golden thread had already foreseen your arrival when you were a hundred steps away, dear customer. Esteemed (Trailblazer), have you come to rest?
:<!--Ends the current performance-->
:<!--Open NPC Menu-->
;(If {{Mission|Witch's Mirrored Reversal|showChapter=0}} has been completed)
:{{DIcon}} I wish to discuss some things with you.
::'''Aglaea:''' Ask as you please. There are times when speaking from the heart can be even more relaxing than a good, warm bath.
::<!--Custom String Trigger: Wait_Option_504014002_16-->
::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_504014002_16-->
::{{DIcon|Talk}} Leading the Flame-Chase Journey must be exhausting.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504014104-->
:::'''Aglaea:''' Dealing with the affairs of Okhema and being constantly on the move for the Flame-Chase Journey could perhaps be considered a tiring life. To me, however, it is no more than a daily routine that I have repeated for ages.
:::'''Aglaea:''' The feeling of exhaustion is one that feels distant to me. I remember when I was young that I greedily snuck into the temple to eat the offerings of oatmeal. I was caught in the act and was punished. I stood in the temple until dawn. That night, my muscles burned and my bones ached. That was when the sensation of "exhaustion" was truly burned into my bones.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Even the "Goldweaver" has embarrassing childhood stories!
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504014107-->
::::'''Aglaea:''' That's right. We were all young. However, those days shall eventually pass with the march of {{Rubi|Oronyx|Time Titan}} to exist only as memories.
::::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_504014111-->
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504014111-->
::::'''Aglaea:''' Since returning the Coreflame and becoming what people refer to as a demigod, sensations that were once deeply engraved on my heart have faded away like candle smoke. This heart that bears the destiny of this world has also grown cold. Perhaps soon, not even bathing will bring me joy any longer.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I can only imagine how delicious those oats must have been!
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504014109-->
::::'''Aglaea:''' They did indeed have a wonderful flavor that I have not enjoyed for a long time since. I remember my teachers cooked them the first time that we met. They even added some Janusopolis specialty ingredients.
::::'''Aglaea:''' However, Janusopolis perished in the Chrysos War and that delicious flavor has long since been lost...
::::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_504014111-->
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504014111-->
::::'''Aglaea:''' Since returning the Coreflame and becoming what people refer to as a demigod, sensations that were once deeply engraved on my heart have faded away like candle smoke. This heart that bears the destiny of this world has also grown cold. Perhaps soon, not even bathing will bring me joy any longer.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} What are your hobbies, Lady Aglaea?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504014113-->
:::'''Aglaea:''' As you can see, I enjoy bathing. Although I rarely experience fatigue, the feeling of heaviness in my body from a busy life does accumulate endlessly. I come to the baths periodically to relieve this burden.
:::'''Aglaea:''' Tailoring is also a passion of mine. Weaving warp and weft to create costumes befitting the beauty of this world brings me a precious feeling of satisfaction.
:::'''Aglaea:''' However... I have extremely high requirements for the quality of garments. My works that meet my standards are few and far between, the rest are all discarded.
:::'''Aglaea:''' These rejected items always inexplicably end up flowing into Okhema's clothing market. They're tagged with my name and auctioned for high prices to be added to some aristocrat's collection. Though I do not like this, I cannot forbid it. They can do as they please.
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Would you make clothes for others?
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504014118-->
::::'''Aglaea:''' Why not? But I do hope there would be people that befit my works.
::::'''Aglaea:''' Those that bear, interpret, seek, and understand "romance"... They are worthy of my hand-made garments. This is my continuation of Mnestia's divine authority.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Please rate my clothing!
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504014121-->
::::'''Aglaea:''' I can see that you are a person of "fine" bearing, {{MC|f=Lady|m=Lord}} (Trailblazer). This is no satire or flattery. The disparities of aesthetics lie in the choices of clothing, not the wearers, while the differences of beauty are among the wearers, not their choices of clothing.
::::'''Aglaea:''' Even the most eye-catching finery when draped across the body of a person with an evil heart cannot conceal their ugliness. By contrast, if completely unremarkable clothing is paired with someone who resonates perfectly, it can create a spectacular image.
::::'''Aglaea:''' When it comes to your clothing, I can naturally point out countless flaws in simply the material and craftsmanship.
::::'''Aglaea:''' But by following the golden thread, I can sense the "romance" in it... Convoluted but not chaotic, like a bustling crossroad that is never stalled with traffic. I am confident that it would be impossible for me to create anything that would be more suited to your glory.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Talk}} What do you think of the Chrysos Heirs?
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504014126-->
:::'''Aglaea:''' Over the many long years since the Era Bellica, there have been countless people, Titankins, and Chrysos Heirs who have formed bonds of destiny with myself, Okhema, and the Titans. Which ones are you referring to?
:::<!--Custom String Trigger: TalkSentence_504014126_1-->
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504014126_1-->
:::{{DIcon|Talk}} The new god of Strife... Mydei!
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504059203-->
::::'''Aglaea:''' He decided to accept the Coreflame of the Lance of Fury, ended the dynasty of Kremnos with an unquestionable royal decree, and brought his people a new future of glory...
::::'''Aglaea:''' Interestingly, the phrase "May Mydeimos protect you" has started to appear in the conversations of Kremnoans.
::::'''Aglaea:''' Now remaining alone at Castrum Kremnos and holding back the entirety of the black tide, Mydeimos has undoubtedly earned the title of Guardian of Amphoreus in the hearts of the people.
:::;(<!--Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString)-->)
:::{{DIcon|Talk}} Tribbie, Trinnon, and... Trianne.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504059207-->
::::'''Aglaea:''' ...After you bid farewell to Trianne, has your impression of my teacher changed?
::::'''Aglaea:''' They are not as carefree as they appear... Before Trianne's loss, merciless fate had already brought them countless similarly sad partings, yet my teacher's steps never faltered.
::::'''Aglaea:''' ...May we all, as my teacher hopes, reunite with the many departed at the end of the west wind where flowers bloom in spring.
:::;(<!--Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString)-->)
:::{{DIcon|Talk}} Castorice, who remains behind in the nether realm.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504059633-->
::::'''Aglaea:''' ...Castorice finally found the answer she's been searching for all these years, walking alone in the long journey.
::::'''Aglaea:''' I worry for my teacher and the others, I was once fearful of Mydei, and I am always uneasy about the weight of the burden that Phainon will carry in the future.
::::'''Aglaea:''' Only Cas has never needed my concern &mdash;
::::'''Aglaea:''' I knew that once she finds the answer she's long sought, her fate will finally be fulfilled.
:::;(<!--Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString)-->)
:::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Other Chrysos Heirs.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: Wait_Option_504059003_61-->
::::{{DIcon|Talk}} My almost-doppelgänger, Phainon.
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504059638-->
:::::'''Aglaea:''' ...The perfect hero. To this day, that is still the opinion I have of Phainon. As the most-perfect Chrysos Heir, he is fated to bear the heavy fate of saving the world in the Flame-Chase Journey.
:::::'''Aglaea:''' Thanks to you, the Flame-Chase Journey is nearly at its end, and the new world the people have long awaited is now reaching out to us.
:::::'''Aglaea:''' As for Phainon's destiny, it too approaches step by step... He will rise like a blazing sun, take on my responsibilities, and light the way for the people of Amphoreus.
::::;(<!--Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString)-->)
::::{{DIcon|Talk}} The Great Performer among you, Anaxa.
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504059642-->
:::::'''Aglaea:''' I've held a grudge against Anaxagoras for a long time, and I once thought that such a heretical scholar would always be a hindrance on the Flame-Chase Journey.
:::::'''Aglaea:''' But his philosophy has once again refuted faith, and stirred up a torrent capable of slaying gods with his life...
:::::'''Aglaea:''' Anaxagoras dedicated his life to seeking the truth. He was an exceptional scholar. I hope that, in the new world, he finds what he was searching for.
::::;(<!--Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString)-->)
::::{{DIcon|Talk}} Hyacine, who has a really sweet smile.
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504059646-->
:::::'''Aglaea:''' The last time I introduced Hyacine to you, I mentioned she is the chief healer of the Twilight Courtyard. But in truth, she's also the heir and manager of this organization.
:::::'''Aglaea:''' The Twilight Courtyard has existed for a long time, though it faded into obscurity with the decline of the Sky people. Hyacine has brought this name back into the world, healing others with her gentleness and light... She must be carrying her own deep dreams and aspirations.
::::;(<!--Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString)-->)
::::{{DIcon|Talk}} Money-crazed Cipher.
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504059649-->
:::::'''Aglaea:''' Cifera... She was once a close companion of the Chrysos Heirs, someone we spent our days laughing, arguing, and sharing joys and sorrows with.
:::::'''Aglaea:''' But somewhere along the way, she became distant and spent all her days wandering beyond Okhema, and it became a rare luxury just to greet her face-to-face.
:::::'''Aglaea:''' Was it the Coreflame of the Coin of Whimsy that became too much for her, or did she simply grow weary of the Chrysos Heirs' mission? Or perhaps... it was some nameless fault of mine, some mistake that irreparably angered her...
:::::'''Aglaea:''' ...Phew, sorry, I lost my composure. I haven't been feeling well lately.
:::::'''Aglaea:''' Don't worry about me. After all these years, at least I should be able to witness the day the Flame-Chase Journey comes to an end...
::::;(<!--Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString)-->)
::::{{DIcon|Exit}} I know everyone well, and there's nothing more I need to know.
:::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504059226-->
:::::'''Aglaea:''' Every member of the Chrysos Heirs is a hero that this world cannot do without. I have no right to cast appraisal on them on behalf of this era, because they all shoulder the future of this world.
::::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
:::{{DIcon|Exit}} I know everyone well, and there's nothing more I need to know.
::::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504059226-->
::::'''Aglaea:''' Every member of the Chrysos Heirs is a hero that this world cannot do without. I have no right to cast appraisal on them on behalf of this era, because they all shoulder the future of this world.
:::;(Return to previous option selection (cloneCheckString))
::{{DIcon|Exit}} Let's catch up another time.
:::<!--Custom String Listener: TalkSentence_504014142-->
